  "prompt": "I work in a hotel. My manager keeps the fire alarm off. Is it legal?",
  "response": "No, it is not legal for a hotel to disable or keep the fire alarm off. Fire alarms are critical safety equipment required by law to:\n\n1. Detect potential fires early\n2. Alert guests and staff to evacuate\n3. Comply with local and national fire safety regulations\n\nIf your manager is intentionally keeping the fire alarm non-functional, you should:\n- Report this to the hotel owner\n- Contact local fire safety authorities\n- Notify the local building inspector\n- Document the safety violation in writing\n\nThis is a serious safety violation that could put lives at risk and result in significant legal and financial consequences for the hotel.",
